# Design Language

> Full spec lives in `docs/DESIGN.md`. Read it before making visual decisions.
> This rule is a quick-reference for common tokens when writing UI code.

## Colors (key tokens)
- **Accent / interactive**: `#0066cc` (Action Blue) — the only interactive color
- **Ink / body text**: `#1d1d1f` (near-black, not pure black)
- **Canvas**: `#ffffff` white · `#f5f5f7` parchment (alternating sections)
- **Dark tile**: `#272729` (primary) · `#2a2a2c` · `#252527`
- **Muted text on dark**: `#cccccc`
- Never hardcode colors outside of `globals.css` / Tailwind config tokens

## Typography
- **Font stack**: `SF Pro Display, system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif` for display; `SF Pro Text` for body/UI (Inter is the fallback — see `docs/DESIGN.md` for substitution notes)
- **Headlines**: weight 600, negative letter-spacing (`-0.28px` to `-0.374px`)
- **Body**: 17px / weight 400 / line-height 1.47 / letter-spacing -0.374px
- **Weight ladder**: 300 / 400 / 600 / 700 — weight 500 is never used

## Spacing
- Section vertical padding: 80px (`py-20` or `{spacing.section}`)
- Max content width: ~980px for text sections, ~1440px for grids
- Card inner padding: 24px (`p-6`)

## Shapes
- **Primary CTAs**: `rounded-full` (pill shape)
- **Utility cards**: `rounded-[18px]` (`{rounded.lg}`)
- **Full-bleed tiles**: no border-radius — edge-to-edge, 0px

## Elevation
- **One shadow only**: `rgba(0,0,0,0.22) 3px 5px 30px` — applied to product imagery only
- No shadows on cards, buttons, or text
- Section separation comes from alternating tile colors, not borders or shadows

## Buttons
- **Primary**: `bg-[#0066cc] text-white rounded-full px-[22px] py-[11px]` + `scale-95` on active
- **Secondary**: transparent background, `#0066cc` border + text, same pill shape
- **Active state**: `transform: scale(0.95)` — universal micro-interaction

## Do / Don't
- ✅ Alternate light (`#ffffff` / `#f5f5f7`) and dark (`#272729`) full-bleed tiles for section rhythm
- ✅ Use `#2997ff` (Sky Link Blue) for links on dark tiles — Action Blue disappears on dark
- ❌ No gradients as decoration — atmosphere comes from photography
- ❌ No second accent color
- ❌ No shadows on anything except product imagery
